  "description": "Once a wild Shockling turns into a Thundring, it grows a pair of mighty wings and takes to the skies. From then on, it will spend the bulk of its time in flight. Wild Thundrings gather around storm clouds, absorbing their electrical energy. While hunting, a Thundring will swoop down and unleash this energy on unsuspecting prey, like a living lightning bolt. This is why the traditional Baltu'kud language uses the same word for both Thundrings and real lightning strikes.",
